text: Tikrachikuyqa yapan hukniraq musuq genética nisqata, chay akllasqataq huñusqanmanta chinkachipun.
translated_text:
Ayacucho Quechua: Turquiaqa mama qachawan muyurisqa kimsa kuchunpi: Egeo qucha quntiman, yana qucha chinchayninman hinataq Mediteraneo quchawan qullanpi. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Ayacucho Quechua: Hatun awqanakuy qallariptinmi yaku hanayninpi submarinukuna purirqa, ichaqa chay radarkuna qispiruptin submarinukuna yaykurqun mama qucha ukuman purinanpaq. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Ayacucho Quechua: Tikrachikuyqa yapan hukniraq musuq genética nisqata, chay akllasqataq huñusqanmanta chinkachipun. 
English: They were the first to use radar to navigate and to detect submarines.
clean_output: They were the first to use radar to navigate and to detect submarines.

Ayacucho Quechua: Turquiaqa mama qachawan muyurisqa kimsa kuchunpi: Egeo qucha quntiman, yana qucha chinchayninman hinataq Mediteraneo quchawan qullanpi. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

English: They were the most advanced submarines in the world at the time.
clean_output: They were the most advanced submarines in the world at the time.

English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Ayacucho Quechua: Turquiaqa mama qachawan muyurisqa kimsa kuchunpi: Egeo qucha quntiman, yana qucha chinchayninman hinataq Mediteraneo quchawan qullanpi. 
English: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.

Ayacucho Quechua: Hatun awqanakuy qallariptinmi yaku hanayninpi submarinukuna purirqa, ichaqa chay radarkuna qispiruptin submarinukuna yaykurqun mama qucha ukuman purinanpaq. 
English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.

Ayacucho Quechua: Suyu qawana pacha kuyuy Geológica Internacional de los Estados Unidos nisqa tapukuna, manam rikuchimunchu ima pacha kuyuytapas Islandiapi chay simanapi. 
English: The island is the largest of the three main islands of the group, and is the only one that is inhabited.
clean_output: The island is the largest of the three main islands of the group, and is the only one that is inhabited.

text: Samaspa huk kaqnin urqu hawanpi La Meca hanaylawninpis, machaysi sapallan karuyasqa tiqsimuyumanta.
